    "headline": "ADM reports Q4 and full-year 2025 results, provides 2026 guidance with increased dividend.",
    "narrative_summary": "Archer-Daniels-Midland Company reported fourth quarter and full-year 2025 financial results, with adjusted EPS of $0.87 for Q4 and $3.43 for the full year. The company provided 2026 adjusted EPS guidance of $3.60 to $4.25, contingent on U.S. biofuel policy clarity. ADM announced a 2% increase in its quarterly dividend, marking its 53rd consecutive year of dividend growth. The company highlighted challenges from global trade uncertainty and biofuel policy deferral, but noted strong cash flow generation and cost-saving initiatives."
